plot: V.I.P. tries to get media mogul Balek as client but ends doing near pro bono protection for a journalist making an exposé on Balek and claiming a car bomb was from Balek.

The VIP team tries to interest media tycoon Viktor Balek to become their client. However measly Internet documentary maker Arnie Feign begs for their services pro bono, claiming Balek wants him killed by Thursday, when he'll have exposed him, which the professionals reject as paranoia. After Arnie's car is blown up, Val makes them agree: he can repay their services in kind, as Internet advertisement.—KGF Vissers
